-- FACTBOX: Key facts about March auto sales
-- 
-- Tue Apr 1, 2008 8:50pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/04/02/us-usa-autosales-idUSN0132025320080402

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - March auto sales fell 12 percent from a year earlier on an unadjusted basis, according to data from auto manufacturers on Tuesday. The following are highlights from the largest carmakers in the U.S. market. 

 Overall industry * Total light vehicle sales -- 1.36 million units. * First quarter sales -- 3.6 million units, down 8 percent. General Motors Corp ( GM.N ) * Light vehicle sales down adjusted 12.7 percent (277,751 units), unadjusted sales down 19 percent * Year-to-date sales down 9.7 percent * Inventories at month-end: 874,000 units * Cars/trucks: Car sales down adjusted 8 percent/light truck sales down 15.7 percent * Retail/fleet mix: retail 77 pct, 23 percent fleet * Market share: 20.7 percent including Saab * Key vehicles: Chevrolet Impala up 9.6 percent, Chevrolet Malibu up 7.3 percent, Chevrolet Silverado down 17.6 percent, Chevrolet Tahoe down 29.1 percent, GMC Sierra up 3.9 percent. * Incentives: average $3,271 per vehicle, up from $2,832 a year earlier. Toyota Motor Corp ( 7203.T )( TM.N ) * Vehicle sales down adjusted 3.4 percent (217,730 units), unadjusted sales down 10 percent * Year-to-date sales down 4.4 percent * Market share: 16 percent * Cars/trucks: Car sales down adjusted 0.2 percent/trucks down 7.7 percent * Key vehicles: Tundra up 16.8 percent, Camry up 3.2 percent, Prius up 16 percent, Corolla down 21.3 percent * Incentives: averaged $898 per vehicle, up from $714 a year earlier. Ford Motor Co ( F.N ) * Vehicle sales down 7.6 percent (227,143 units) on an adjusted basis, unadjusted sales down 14 percent * Inventories at month-end were 562,000 units, down 11,000 units from a year earlier * Retail/fleet sales: Retail sales of Ford, Lincoln, Mercury down 17 percent/total fleet sales down 9 percent on an unadjusted basis * Cars/trucks: Car sales down 3.1 percent/truck sales down 16.7 percent * Market share: 16.7 percent including Jaguar, Land Rover, Volvo * Key vehicles: F-Series down 17.9 percent on an adjusted basis, Ranger up 16.2 percent, Explorer down 8.3 percent, Expedition down 28.6 percent, Focus up 33.6 percent, Fusion up 8.4 percent. * Incentives: averaged $3,017 per vehicle, down from $3,114 a year earlier. Chrysler LLC * Car and light truck sales down adjusted 13.2 percent year over year (166,386 units), unadjusted sales down 19 percent * Cars/trucks: Car sales down 1.1 percent/truck sales down 17.2 percent * Market share: 12.3 percent * Inventories at month-end were 423,607 units, or a 66-day supply, down 76,000 from year ago. * Key vehicles: Jeep Wrangler down 31 percent, Dodge Ram pickup down 26 percent, Dodge Caliber up 18.6 percent. * Incentives: average $4,142 per vehicle, down from $4,237 a year earlier. Honda Motor Co ( 7267.T )( HMC.N ) * Car and light truck sales up adjusted 4.2 percent year-over-year (138,734 vehicles); down 3.2 percent on an unadjusted basis * Market share: 10 percent * Cars/trucks: Cars up 11.1 percent on an adjusted basis/truck sales down 4.7 percent * Key vehicles: Accord up adjusted 6.8 percent, Civic up 19 percent, CR-V up 4 percent. * Incentives: averaged $1,297 per vehicle, up from $1,157 a year earlier. Nissan Motor Co Ltd ( 7201.T ) * Car and light truck sales up adjusted 3.6 percent year over year (106,921); down 3.8 percent unadjusted. * Market share: 7.9 percent * Cars/trucks: Cars up adjusted 15 percent/trucks down 11 percent * Key vehicles: Altima up adjusted 23 percent, Versa up 34 percent, Sentra up 21 percent, Titan down 45 percent, Frontier down 29 percent. * Incentives: average $2,031 per vehicle, down slightly from $2,043 a year earlier. Incentives estimates are provided by industry tracking firm Edmunds.com. Sales comparisons in adjusted terms account for two fewer selling days in March than the same month a year earlier. (Reporting by  Soyoung Kim ,  David Bailey ,  Kevin Krolicki ; Editing by  Braden Reddall )